pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Technology Strategy Board is </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the UK</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">’s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> innovation agency and acts as the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">prime channel through which the Government incentivises business-led technology in</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">novation.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.35pt; padding-left:4.5pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The Technology Strategy Board</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> was </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">established in July 2007</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> and h</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">as </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">committed</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> more than </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">£1</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.3</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> billion</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> to date</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, the majority of the funding being matched by business</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">We have </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">directly supported </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">over 6,500</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> companies and work with </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">nearly</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> every Uni</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">versity in the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">UK.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.35pt; padding-left:4.5pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The commercialisation of research and the support of innovation across the economy is vital to deliver future </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">products and services </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">and to generate economic growth.  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The Technology Strategy Board </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">welcomes the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Committee’s </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">inquiry</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.35pt; padding-left:4.5pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The Technology Strategy Board recognises that </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the low carbon economy</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> pose</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">s significant opportunities</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> for UK businesses to innovate and capitalise</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. It is in response to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">se</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> possibilities that the Technology Strategy Board has created a number of programme</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">s and projects to stimulate </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">low carbon innovation</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.35pt; padding-left:4.5pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The Technology Strategy Board is a founding member of the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">cross-governmental </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Low Carbon Innovation Coordination Group (LCICG).  A joint LCICG response has been </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">submitted outlining</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> the view of that group </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">to the questions raised by the committee, its actions and plans for coordinating support for </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">i</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">nnovation in the sector.  This response </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">should be considered alongside that</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> LCCIG response </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">in</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> adding more </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">detail of the Technology Strategy Board</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">’s aims and activ</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ities, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">highlighting areas of best practice</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.35pt; padding-left:4.5pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The Technology Strategy Board supports low carbon innovation through many of its programmes, but the three thematic focus areas of Energy Generation and Supply, Transport and the Built Environment stimulate </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the majority of the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">low carbon support activity.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.35pt; padding-left:4.5pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The Technology Strategy Board typically commits £25m per year to supporting new energy technology development, £10m per year in built environment, and £20m per year for transport.  In addition to its own bu</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">dget it also leverages funding from other public sources, for example from </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">DECC and</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">DfT</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> in order to provide more joined-up support</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.35pt; padding-left:4.5pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Technology Strategy </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Board’s energy programme is outlined in our energy strategy which can be found at </span><a href="https://www.innovateuk.org/energy"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">https://www.innovateuk.org/energy</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.  The programme focuses on supporting businesses developing new technologies that help solve the energy ‘</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">trilemma</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">’ of security, affordability and sustainability.  Businesses that help solve</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> this challenge will access large future markets.  As a result, nearly all our energy support </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">is allocated to progress </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">low carbon solutions</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.35pt; padding-left:4.5pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The built </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">environment programme includes the Low Impact Buildings Innovation Platform which seeks to join up key stakeholders in joint </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">roadmapping</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> and action plans in order to reduce the carbon impact of buildings.  Recent programmes have included retrofit programme</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">s demonstrating 80% reduction in emissions across a range of housing stock.  More can be found at </span><a href="https://www.innovateuk.org/built-environment"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">https://www.innovateuk.org/built-environment</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The transport programme covers a range of transpor</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">t areas.  The Low Carbon Vehicles Innovation Platform brings together industry and other funders in a coordinated programme of activity that has included the largest ultra-low emissions vehicle </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">demonstrator</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> a £50m programme of over 300 vehicles across 8 l</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ocations, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">which is </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">co-funded with </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">DfT</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> and regional agencies.  The Innovation Platform runs competitions under an Integrated Delivery Programme which aims to integrate the innovation chain from the science base through development and to commercial </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">demonstr</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ation</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">  More information is available at </span><a href="https://www.innovateuk.org/transport#platform"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">https://www.innovateuk.org/transport#platform</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The Technology Strategy Board has launched a network of Catapult Centres designed to help businesses</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> develop and commercialise new technologies faster and more effectively, bridging the gap between concept and commercialisation by providing deep expertise, resource and large scale testing facilities in certain sectors.  Three of the first seven catapult </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">centres are operating in the low carbon area: Offshore Renewable Energy, Future Transport Systems and F</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">uture Cities.  More information is available at</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><a href="https://www.innovateuk.org/-/catapult-centres"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">https://www.innovateuk.org/-/catapult-centres</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.  Two new centres have been recently announced, one of which is Energy Systems.  This centre will be developed for launch </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">in </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">April 2015.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The Technology Strategy Board aims to join its support programmes up as much as it possibly can with other funders</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">  In some cases this is as a formal arrangement via integrated delivery programmes, in other </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">instances this </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">is</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> done</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">as opportunities arise</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.  The Technology Strategy Board sees one of its roles</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> being</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"