isted before in helping to support innovation in the right areas to reduce cost of the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">energy system in </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">future.  More information about TINA is provided in the LCICG submission.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Does the Government have the right balance of focus between energy efficiency, renewable energy and other low carbon technologies? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Technology Strategy </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Board</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">’s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> programmes cover all three of these elements via the programmes described in paragraphs 7-11.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">  It is also important to consider how different areas of the energy system fit together and are integrated effectively in future systems at the lowest cos</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">t.  This is an area that the new Energy Systems Catapult centre will develop expertise in, and which we feel deserves more</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> innovation</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> support in </span><span style="font-family